Key Match Events: Thapelo Morena’s header narrowly missed the mark at the 17th minute
Mazraoui kicked the ball into the net in the 28th minute, but the goal was disallowed due to offside
Evidence Makgopa managed to score a goal in the 55th minute
Ayoub El Kaabi had a good chance with a header in the 75th minute, but it missed the goal
Post-Match Reflections: Rabat - The Moroccan national football team’s journey at the Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) has come to an end after sustaining a 2-0 defeat against South Africa in the tournament’s round of 16.
South Africa will lock horns with Cape Verde in the tournament’s quarterfinals next Saturday.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Despite being favorites to not only win today’s clash but the tournament itself, the Atlas Lions were unable to put the ball in the net against a South African team whose tactics appeared to be to defend in numbers and rely on few counterattacking opportunities to score.
Both teams struggled to break the deadlock in the first half of the game.
The game then turned tetchy, with Kekana receiving a yellow card in the 32nd minute.
Frustration grew on both sides as players missed golden opportunities to score.
Bayen Leverkusen’s Adli missed a good opportunity for the Atlas Lions in the 38th minute.
Ayoub El Kaabi had a good chance with a header in the 75th minute, but it unfortunately missed the goal.
